texts.text: This is it. In there.
Whadda ya mean in there? There's no entrance.
Yo, are you tryin' to double-cross us or something...?
Calm down Megakin. She's not lying.
The flow of Chi here is very peculiar.
Meaning...?
It's like the Aura Gate. Which means I can get you in.
So that's how it works... That's why we couldn't find any evidence in our investigation.
Sorry I doubted you girl. So this is the demon's lair...
Megakin, we're here!
This is the demon's base of operations? I don't see anything here...
I'll handle it. Just give me a minute.
What do you mean? Ah wait, I get it now. It's an Aura Gate thing.

Everyone ready? Just close you're eyes and...
Here we go.
Okay, you can open you're eyes now.
Huh? We're in a... Subway tunnel?
Sure looks like it. But there's nobody around...
There's a weird smell.
Feels like we're being watched.
Yes, the air's pretty foul in here. And the flow of the Chi here is in serious disarray...
It's the enemy's stronghold,
wouldn't be surprised if we are.
Hey Megakin! Can you come here for a second?
I got bad news... Look at the things strewn on the floor around this place, they're all...
>The ground is littered with small pieces of torn clothing and flesh.
>They look to be pieces of human remains, mutilated by whatever it is that ate them...!
Oh man... They're literally in pieces.
Fuck, this goes way beyond just attacking and injuring people...
And from the looks of it, there were a lot more than just a few victims.

!!
Everybody get down!
>Jeng Yun yanks your arm and pulls you to the ground.
>You feel something swoosh by right above your head...
Grrrr, missed!
Pretty fast for a human, but that won't save you!
>The darkness covering the roof stirs to life and breaks into a thousand little pieces!
Oh my god! Those are all bats?!
So... You're the demon users trying to stop my hunt...
That's right. Why're you hunting humans anyway?!
What you've done here is unforgivable no matter what the reason, but I wanna know.

Why? Grrrr...
Because humans are there for the taking that's why!
...Huh?
We used to reside in a deeper darkness,
be one day we were suddenly driven out by an unknown force!

Mad I was, yessss...
Grrrrr...
Suddenly driven out?
I had no choice but to build a new den here,
but this turned out to be quite a good spot. Easy for me to bring in humans
and cut off their heads with these blades of mine!
I just love feasting on them!
THAT'S your reason for killing all these people?

The weak get preyed on, it is natural law...
If you don't want to get eaten, you have to be strong!
Aight, if that's what you believe,
you wouldn't mind if we took you down by force then, would ya?!
Devil... Download!
>The Liberators' fight with Camazotz rages on.
It's using its minions in a defensive position,
which means it's hurt pretty bad. This is our chance to strike!
I'll clear a path! Demons away!
I have a clear shot! Here we go!
Grrr... Gaaaaargh!!
>Camazotz lets out a scream in death and dissipates.

...
It's done.
That should put an end to the bat attacks.
Which leaves the victims...
It's hard to decide what to do with these remains.
We can let the police handle this so maybe some of them can be identified and returned to their families.

But carnage like this...
It'd be too horrifying for them to bear...
It's hard enough to accept the death of a loved one as it is, showing them this would really drive them over the deep end.
Yes, I see where you're coming from...
I understand the sentiment, but there's nothing we can do about it.
Yes there is. We can still cover it up...
We can walk away without reporting this. Then at least their families will have the hope of
"Maybe they're alive" to hang on to.
...What? Are you serious?
...Sorry, my bad. Forget what I said man.
I guess I'm just feelin' sentimental today. A moment of weakness.
Let's leave this to the cops.
You sure are silent today. What's on your mind?
Let me guess, Megakin's dilemma back there?
Whether to hand the victims' remains to the police or cover it up?
It was the right decision.
We should've covered it up.
So that's how you feel.
But I don't think there's a right answer to something like that.
When faced with a choice, people tend to search unconsciously for the right answer.
And even though not every problem has a right answer,
sometimes we still have to make a choice nonetheless. Like we did back there.
The dilemma we faced was not about what's right and what's wrong.
It was a choice between two different ways of thinking, that's all. At least that's what I think...

*Chuckle*
Life's full of difficulties, isn't it?
Yo Seiran, we're all set. The cops will take over from here.
Yo Newbie, what're you still doing here? You didn't go back with the others?
Sorry for making you wait then. C'mon, let's get back to the Hideout.
You okay?
You don't have to be strong all the time, you know?
To tell the truth, it'll take a while for me to get over this.
It's hard, but I have to let it go.
Cuz technically I'm the leader, so I have to put on a brave face.
Hahaha, thanks man. Appreciate it.
I guess I'm not a very good leader if I have you worrying about me.
I kind of need to act strong for now though, or I'll probably fall apart.
Don't worry. Things will be fine once I get things sorted out in my head.
Sorry to interrupt your great heroic speech but...
Very funny Seiran Saikawa. What is it?
Remember how Camazotz's lair was a real place that became a sort of spiritual world?
And what Camazotz said about being driven out?
Yeah, he did say somethin' like that.
I have a feeling that there's more to this than we're seeing right now.
I think I want to investigate further into this area, just in case.
I just hope this feeling I have turns out to be a false alarm.
Aight, I look forward to hearing your report say that it was nothing after all then.
*Pant*

>In a maze-like underground
passageway, a man is running.
Exit. Where's the exit...
How did this happen? Why was I...

*Pant*
Doesn't matter, I have to get away...!
>The man keeps running, throwing anxious glances behind him as he goes.
>Then he turns a corner and is forced to stop.

A dead end...
N-No.
Somebody please help me! Get me out of here, I beg you!
I'm dead if I get caught by-!
Before I get caught by...
>Sensing an evil aura coming up behind him, the man freezes in mid-sentence.
Oh no... T-This isn't what it looks like. I wasn't trying to escape. I swear.

So can we just...!
Wait, no! I didn't mean to...
>The walls and floor of the closed passageway begins to change shape,
>turning into countless needles and spikes...
Wait, please don't kill... me...!
>The man is pierced through and through like a rag doll.
>Taking one last look at the man's dead body,
>the pursuer turns around and vanishes into the depths of the underground facility.
To be continued...?
